content: I've used this ap for a few years now and it has always worked well.
Brilliant variations
The best ever!
Invaluable for processing films at room temperature..

Used this to develop a roll of 120 Ilford hp5 plus on d-76, and it came out way over exposed. I thought it was my mistake with a new type of film, but then I checked the development times for tri-x on the same developer, and it was 1 minute and 15 seconds longer than Kodak suggests, they say 5:30, this app says 7:45, you can check it yourself, at 24째. So, essentially the one thing that this app is meant to do, it doesn't. I'm sad that my images were so over exposed as to be essentially unusable.
replyContent: I've checked the development time for this combination. The Ilford Film Processing Chart says: HP5+ in D76 (1+1) at 68째f = 11 min. Looking at the Ilford Temperature Compensation Chart for 78째f the time reduces to 6:15 min, for 80f to 6:00 min. For the Kodak time it seems that you've looked up the time for stock solution (1+0).

content: Great functionality, horrible usability. The data and functions in the app are great and what one would want and like. But the usability makes it impossible to use. Everytime I made a mistake I had to completely exit the app and restart what you were doing.
replyContent: Why do you need to restart the app? Which mistakes can one do that one has to restart the app? It would be nice if you could explain the problem to me per email...

content: Does its job!

Pretty clunky interface. The timer is really bare bones. The lack of a pause /resume button on the timer is a huge miss. Also the lack of screen rotation. Most of the screen is taken over by the control interface not the timer and the black on red is not really darkroom safe. Red on black would be better. Also time is way off for Bergger 400 in XTOL - not the manufacturers specifications.
replyContent: I've checked the dev times for Bergger Pancro 400 and Bergger BRF 400 in XTOL. The times are correct like specified by the manufacturer. Please be sure you set up ISO, dilution, temperature and agitation correctly. If you want red on black darkroom mode please switch to one of the dark theme. Thank you very much for your review.

content: So useful!!

Good app, overall. The flexibility to create a fully customized chain of steps is fantastic. One request would be to have it pop up a message that it can't find a valid time for a given combination of developer + film. As it is, the app sits there, showing you a blank timer, and refusing to allow you to save as a favorite, with no explanation. Worse, if you rearrange the process to add a pre-soak step before the main timer (which is great that you can!), then the developer timer crashes out leaving you staring at a useless screen while trying to remember how many seconds it's been, and trying desperately to sync up to a digital clock nearby while you switch over to a stopwatch app and try to get it sync'd to the nearest 30 seconds. So a validation check on each step of the process would be helpful. :)
replyContent: Thank you very much for the good description of the bug. I've fixed the issue in the new version of the app.

content: Could do with clear instructions as not all film and developer combinations will calculate a developing time for you and allow you to start the timer. In these instances you should look up the massive Dev chart online and enter the dev time manually on this app. Otherwise the app seems to work well.
replyContent: For some combinations of film and developer there are no developing times known and hence there's no entry in the database. For such combinations the app don't show developing times and you cannot start the timer as long as you don't set the developing time manually.

content: Extensive lists, highly accurate development times.
My goto film developing app
How can I stop a time and advance to the next process step?
replyContent: Just press the back button of your device and you will see the dialog were you can advance to the next process step.

Good

Great app

I use this app very frequently and - by and large - the recommendations are very good. Strongly recommended.

Incredibly handy When developing, times can be set for a pre wash, the actual development, a second wash, fixer, and a final wash (my process). It's totally customizable and has every film I've ever wanted to use in it.
Perfect!!!

User Interface is a bit clunky and not that intuitive but the app does a good job once you get used to it. A button to reset all search-parameters at once - like developer/ ASA / agitation rhythm etc. - would be nice. Right now you have to reset every value yourself, because the grey checkmarks only help if you type in the parameters in a specific order. A simple way to reset the values would earn the app the 5th star. Nevertheless, definitely the best app out there.
replyContent: Thank you for the review. If all parameters selected and you switch one of them than the checkmarks show you if there's a time in the database, regardless of the order you typed in the parameters. If at least one parameter is not selected and you switch another one, the checkmarks may not be reliable. However, resetting all params is a good idea.

Excellent! It works again now. Previous issue: "I used to be able to obtain "projected" time when I changed the dilution and temperature, e.g. it gave shorter developing time when I change the temperature from 24C to 28C, the results were always acceptable. Now this feature doesn't work. For example, developing Ilford Pan F Plus film using Ilfotec DD-X at 24C gets a 05:00 minutes time but changing the temperature to 28C would get a ~05:00 minutes. Changing developer dilution has similar result."
replyContent: Thank you very much for reporting this issue. I've fixed the bug already.

content: I like the audible warning that the agitation period is approaching.

replyContent: Thank you for your feedback. In the past 15 days the only crashes I received were from a Lenovo YOGA A12 device. It seems that they're your crashes. These crashes have their origin in the system libraries of this device. I'll check if this crashes can be avoided for this device.

It's good. But!!  don't use the Kodak tri x with id-11 times are off by 3mins plus
replyContent: I checked the dev times for this combination and they are equal to the recommandations of both the Ilford processing chart of ID-11 as well as the Kodak processing chart of D-76. Please double check the times and be sure you select the right push, dilution, temperature and agitation. You may select the old version of Tri-X instead of Prof. Tri-X?

content: I developed black and white film for years just using general guidelines and watching a clock. This app adds a good deal more precision to the process, I can quickly and EASILY adjust for temperature of the chemicals, push or pull the film, compensate for different dilutions, etc.  Do you need this app? No, of course not; but it makes experimenting easier and helps add more precision into the process. I find it very useful and love the database with all the different films I use.
